===Etymology===
Late Latin '''hypocorisma''', a loan from Greek noun υποκόρισμα ('''hypokórisma''') from the verb 'υπο-κορίζομαι ('''hypokórizomai''' = 'to talk and handle at a childish manner'). The Greek verb ''hypokorízomai'' is compounded from 'υπο- ([[hypo-]] = 'under, beneath, secretly') + κοριζομαι (korizomai = 'to [[caress]]'). In the verb you can see the word κόρος (kóros = '[[boy]]') or κόρη (kóre = '[[girl]]').

